The paper deals with a wireless communication intervention problem at the physical layer, which falls under the scope of information theory (cs.IT). The problem involves a malicious link and spoofing, which are related to computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses power allocation and interference, which are relevant to networked systems (cs.NI) and multimedia systems (cs.MM). Finally, the proposed combined spoofing approach involves optimization, which is a common theme in control systems (cs.SY).
